19/10/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Justice Minister Ana Lovrin defended the success of judicial reforms Thursday (October 18th), noting that the number of unresolved court cases has been slashed by more than 500,000 during the past two years.
She added that the number of verdicts in corruption cases has increased by 120%, suggesting the anti-corruption strategy is being implemented consistently.
Lovrin pointed out that the introduction of obligatory asset declarations for all judges and state prosecutors has been a key measure.
(Vjesnik - 19/10/07;
HINA - 18/10/07)
